Installing ARM cross compiler toolchain to build linux kernel

Download tool chain ,
http://releases.linaro.org/components/toolchain/binaries/

Linaro is free and open-source software such as the Linux kernel, the GNU Compiler Collection (GCC), power management, 
graphics and multimedia interfaces for the ARM family of instruction sets and implementations thereof as well as for the 
Heterogeneous System Architecture. 

# sudo tar xvf gcc-linaro-5.4.1-2017.05-x86_64_arm-linux-gnueabihf.tar.xz -C /opt/
# cd /opt/
# sudo mv gcc-linaro-arm-linux-gnueabihf-4.8-2014.04_linux/ gcc-arm-linux
# export PATH=$PATH:/opt/gcc-arm-linux/bin

Check

# locate arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc
/opt/gcc-arm-linux/bin/arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc
/opt/gcc-arm-linux/bin/arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc-5.4.1
/opt/gcc-arm-linux/bin/arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc-ar
/opt/gcc-arm-linux/bin/arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc-nm
/opt/gcc-arm-linux/bin/arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc-ranlib
/opt/gcc-arm-linux/share/man/man1/arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc.1

# arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc --version
